Background
Crédit Nationale Azur is a newly established French bank in Melbourne. Last year, they launched a campaign offering personal loans at very competitive rates to their customers, and about 15% of the customers approach took a personal loan. They now wish to launch a similar campaign. However, instead of blindly approaching all of their customers, they wish to use a more targeted approach to reduce the costs involved and increase their chances of success. In order to do so, they need to understand the characteristics of the customers who took the loan and, based on the characteristics, predict which customers are more likely to take personal loans.

As a recent graduate of the BBus (Information Systems) program, you were hired as part of the graduate program of Crédit Nationale Azur, and since you have excellent analytics skills, you were posted to the data science team. Your team leader has assigned the personal loan project to you.

The dataset for last year's promotional campaign is available to you. It has also been labelled in terms of who accepted or rejected personal loan offers made to them. A data dictionary describing the data items is also available.

There are several ways to analyse the data; however, as an initial step, your brief is to use appropriate machine learning algorithms for creating a model for predicting which customers are likely to accept offers for a personal loan and identify the characteristics of these customers.

At a high level, the deliverables for this project are:

A technical report explaining and justifying the analysis and design decisions made during the various phases of this data science project, as well as the best practices used. (6%).
Python code (in Jupyter Notebooks) used for all phases of the project. (30%)
A business report presenting your findings and providing recommendations to the management of the bank. (4%).
